CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 1, 1941, pg. 9 reads: "Cutting Birthday Cake - Charming Miss Grace Redd of Lowell street observed her birthday Saturday with much gayety and a party to which Eddie Breckman was host. Miss Redd wore gardenias and was felicitated and showered with gifts by many friends - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Grace Redd wearing dark dress with spaghetti straps, cross necklace, and corsage, posed with cake with candles, in interior with dark trim on doors
